FBIS3-7588 "dreas061_a_94010" FBIS-EAS-94-061 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Government Plans To Make Loan to Bangladesh OW2903085494 Tokyo KYODO in English 0813 GMT 29 Mar 94 OW2903085494 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tokyo, March 29 KYODO -- Japan will extend to Bangladesh a 21 billion yen official loan during the visit to Japan by Prime Minister Begum Khaleda Ziaur, who arrived in Tokyo on Monday [28 March], the Foreign Ministry said Tuesday. The ministry said in a press release that the 21.56 billion yen in official development assistance (ODA) will go toward construction of a bridge over the Jamuna River, which divides the country into the east and west regions.
